            <div class="article-faq">
                <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Why does my converted Word document look different from the PDF?</summary>
                    <p>PDFs store content as positioned elements rather than flowing text, so converters have to reconstruct document structure through inference. Complex layouts, multi-column text, and unusual fonts are the most common sources of formatting differences after conversion.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Can I convert a password-protected PDF to Word?</summary>
                    <p>You need to unlock the PDF first. Use PdfToolStack's <a href="/unlock-pdf">Unlock PDF tool</a> to remove the password, then convert the unlocked file to Word.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Will my images be included in the Word document?</summary>
                    <p>Yes. Images embedded in the PDF are preserved as image objects in the Word document. They won't be editable as graphics, but they'll appear in the correct position. Charts from Excel or PowerPoint that were embedded in the PDF will also appear as images.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Is PDF to Word conversion free?</summary>
                    <p>Yes — PdfToolStack's PDF to Word conversion is completely free for files under 25MB with no signup required. Pro users can convert files up to 500MB and use batch conversion for multiple files simultaneously.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>How do I convert a Word document back to PDF?</summary>
                    <p>In Word, go to File → Save As → choose PDF from the format dropdown. Alternatively, use PdfToolStack's <a href="/word-to-pdf">Word to PDF converter</a> for consistent results without needing Word installed.</p>
                </details>
